              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=canadian-bingo-2020">canadian-bingo-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/39134508-kathleen?shelf=suspense">suspense</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2018021919" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7811938811603697119">&quot;Clara Morrow had painted the moment despair became hope. <br/>Francois Marois stepped back half a pace and nodded gravely. <br/>&quot;It&apos;s remarkable. Beautiful.&quot; He turned to Gamache then. &quot;Unless, of course, it&apos;s a ruse.&quot;<br/>&quot;What do you mean?&quot; asked Gamache. <br/>&quot;Maybe it isn&apos;t hope at all,&quot; said Marois, &quot;but merely a trick of the light.&quot;&apos;<br/><br/>A Trick Of The Light is the seventh novel in A Chief Inspector Gamache series. Please read the books in order and do not skip any. When you miss a book, you do not get the full u</span>
  <span id="freeText7811938811603697119" style="display:none">"Clara Morrow had painted the moment despair became hope. <br />Francois Marois stepped back half a pace and nodded gravely. <br />"It's remarkable. Beautiful." He turned to Gamache then. "Unless, of course, it's a ruse."<br />"What do you mean?" asked Gamache. <br />"Maybe it isn't hope at all," said Marois, "but merely a trick of the light."'<br /><br />A Trick Of The Light is the seventh novel in A Chief Inspector Gamache series. Please read the books in order and do not skip any. When you miss a book, you do not get the full understanding of the stories and miss out on the added pleasure the novel has to offer. <br />I enjoy learning while reading, and usually learn something interesting from Louise Penny's books. This time I was pleased to learn more about art, art galleries, and the art world, and also a bit about AA. <br /><br />"Hearts are broken," Lillian Dyson underlined in a book. "Sweet relationships are dead." But now Lillian is dead in Clara Morrow's garden, shattering the celebrations of Clara's solo show at the famed Musee d'Art Contemporain in Montreal. Chief inspector Gamache, the head of homicide at the Surete du Quebec, is called to the tiny Quebec village of Three Pines and there he finds a world of shading and nuance, shadow and light. And even when facts are slowly exposed, it is no longer clear to the Gamache and his team if what they found is the truth, or simply a trick of the light.<br />4.5 rounded up to 5 stars<br /><br /><br />Huge thanks to Annapolis Valley Regional Library and the librarians, who manage, organize and keep the libraries running, for the loan of this book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7811938811603697119" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


